About Groestlcoin

Launched in Mar 2014, Groestlcoin (GRS) is an ASIC-resistant peer-to-peer (p2p) cryptocurrency that claims to offer very low fees. GRS was reportedly one of the first few coins to implement Segregated Witness (SegWit) and perform a Lightning Network transaction on its network. GRS utilizes two rounds of Grstl-512 for its mining algorithm, and rose to prominence during the Bitcoin fork in late 2017 as CPU/GPU miners sought to move away from coins dominated by ASIC miners.
